com.xtructure.xutil.id
Class XId

java.lang.Object
  com.xtructure.xutil.id.XId
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<XId>
Direct Known Subclasses:
XValId
public class XId
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<XId>

An identifier with hierarchical information in the form of a trailing list of instance numbers.

Where "EXAMPLE:[0,1,2]" is an id for some object, its parent's id would be "EXAMPLE:[0,1]", one of its sibling's id might be "EXAMPLE:[0,1,5]", and one of its child's id might be "EXAMPLE:[0,1,2,88]".

"EXAMPLE" is still a valid id, representing some root object of the hierarchy.

Author:
Peter Nürnberg, Luis Guimbarda
